## SpectralNotify Design Tokens & Auth Styling

Use CSS variables and OKLCH tokens. Do not hard-code hex colors. Map SpectralChat guidance to spectralNotify auth pages and shared UI.

### Where tokens are defined
- Web globals: [apps/web/src/index.css](mdc:apps/web/src/index.css)
  - Provides semantic tokens `--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, `--secondary`, `--ring`, `--border`, sidebar tokens, and radius scale via `@theme inline`.
- Button base: [apps/web/src/components/ui/button.tsx](mdc:apps/web/src/components/ui/button.tsx)
  - Variants consume semantic tokens (e.g., `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, `focus-visible:ring-ring/50`).

### Auth screens consuming styles
